skills.name: Glistening Light
skills.simple_desc: Deals minor Lightning DMG to a single enemy.
skills.desc: Jing Yuan deals Lightning DMG equal to 80% of his ATK to a single enemy.

skills.name: Rifting Zenith
skills.simple_desc: Deals minor Lightning DMG to all enemies and increases Lightning-Lord's Hits Per Action.
skills.desc: Deals Lightning DMG equal to 93% of Jing Yuan's ATK to all enemies and increases Lightning-Lord's Hits Per Action by 2 for the next turn.

skills.name: Lightbringer
skills.simple_desc: Deals Lightning DMG to all enemies and increases Lightning-Lord's Hits Per Action.
skills.desc: Deals Lightning DMG equal to 190% of Jing Yuan's ATK to all enemies and increases Lightning-Lord's Hits Per Action by 3 for the next turn.

skills.name: Prana Extirpated
skills.desc:
Summons Lightning-Lord at the start of the battle. Lightning-Lord has 60 base SPD and 3 base Hits Per Action. When the Lightning-Lord takes action, its hits are considered as follow-up attacks, with each hit dealing Lightning DMG equal to 66% of Jing Yuan's ATK to a random single enemy, and enemies adjacent to it also receive Lightning DMG equal to 25% of the DMG dealt to the target enemy.
The Lightning-Lord's Hits Per Action can reach a max of 10. Every time Lightning-Lord's Hits Per Action increases by 1, its SPD increases by 10. After the Lightning-Lord's action ends, its SPD and Hits Per Action return to their base values.
When Jing Yuan is knocked down, the Lightning-Lord will disappear.
When Jing Yuan is affected by Crowd Control debuff, the Lightning-Lord is unable to take action.

skills.name: Spirit Invocation
skills.desc: After the Technique is used, the Lightning-Lord's Hits Per Action in the first turn increases by 3 at the start of the next battle.

relic_sets.name: Musketeer of Wild Wheat
relic_sets.desc: The wearer's SPD increases by 6% and Basic ATK DMG increases by 10%.

relic_sets.name: Inert Salsotto
relic_sets.desc: Increases the wearer's CRIT Rate by 8%. When the wearer's current CRIT Rate reaches 50% or higher, the wearer's Ultimate and follow-up attack DMG increases by 15%.

skills.name: I Want to Help
skills.simple_desc: Deals minor Physical DMG to a single enemy.
skills.desc: Deals Physical DMG equal to 70% of Clara's ATK to a single enemy.

skills.name: Svarog Watches Over You
skills.simple_desc: Deals Physical DMG to all enemies. Additionally deals Physical DMG to targets with Marks of Counter.
skills.desc:
Deals Physical DMG equal to 105% of Clara's ATK to all enemies, and additionally deals Physical DMG equal to 105% of Clara's ATK to enemies marked by Svarog with a Mark of Counter.
All Marks of Counter will be removed after this Skill is used.

skills.name: Promise, Not Command
skills.simple_desc: Reduces DMG received, increases chance to be attacked by enemies, and enhances Counters.
skills.desc:
After Clara uses Ultimate, DMG dealt to her is reduced by an extra 22%, and she has greatly increased chances of being attacked by enemies for 2 turn(s).
In addition, Svarog's Counter is enhanced. When an ally is attacked, Svarog immediately launches a Counter, and its DMG multiplier against the enemy increases by 144%. Enemies adjacent to it take 50% of the DMG dealt to the target enemy. Enhanced Counter(s) can take effect 2 time(s).

skills.name: Because We're Family
skills.simple_desc: DMG received from enemy attacks is reduced. Enemies who attack Clara will be marked with a Mark of Counter and met with Svarog's Counter, dealing Physical DMG.
skills.desc: Under the protection of Svarog, DMG taken by Clara when hit by enemy attacks is reduced by 10%. Svarog will mark enemies who attack Clara with his Mark of Counter and retaliate with a Counter, dealing Physical DMG equal to 150% of Clara's ATK.

skills.name: A Small Price for Victory
skills.simple_desc: Attacks the enemy. After entering battle, this character's chance of being attacked by enemies increases.
skills.desc: Immediately attacks the enemy. Upon entering battle, the chance Clara will be attacked by enemies increases for 2 turn(s).

relic_sets.desc: Increases the wearer's CRIT Rate by 8%. When the wearer's current CRIT Rate reaches 50% or higher, the wearer's Ultimate and follow-up attack DMG increases by 15%.

skills.name: Behind the Kindness
skills.simple_desc: Deals minor Physical DMG to a single enemy.
skills.desc: Deals Physical DMG equal to 80% of Natasha's ATK to a single enemy.

skills.name: Love, Heal, and Choose
skills.simple_desc: Restores a single ally's HP and continuously heals them.
skills.desc: Restores a single ally for 10.5% of Natasha's Max HP plus 280. Restores the ally for another 7.2% of Natasha's Max HP plus 192 at the beginning of each turn for 2 turn(s).

skills.name: Gift of Rebirth
skills.desc: Heals all allies for 13.8% of Natasha's Max HP plus 368.

skills.name: Innervation
skills.simple_desc: When healing allies with low HP, increases Outgoing Healing. This effect also works on continuous healing.
skills.desc: When healing allies with HP percentage at 30% or lower, increases Natasha's Outgoing Healing by 50%. This effect also works on continuous healing.

skills.name: Hypnosis Research
skills.simple_desc: Attacks the enemy. After entering battle, deals minor Physical DMG to a random single enemy, with a high chance to inflict Weaken to all enemy targets.
skills.desc:
Immediately attacks the enemy. After entering battle, deals Physical DMG equal to 80% of Natasha's ATK to a random enemy, with a 100% base chance to Weaken all enemies.
While Weakened, enemies deal 30% less DMG to allies for 1 turn(s).

relics.name: The Xianzhou Luofu's Ambrosial Arbor Vines

relic_sets.name: Passerby of Wandering Cloud
relic_sets.desc: At the start of the battle, immediately regenerates 1 Skill Point.

relic_sets.name: Fleet of the Ageless
relic_sets.desc: Increases the wearer's Max HP by 12%. When the wearer's SPD reaches 120 or higher, all allies' ATK increases by 8%.

skills.name: System Warning
skills.simple_desc: Deals minor Quantum DMG to a single enemy.
skills.desc: Deals Quantum DMG equal to 50% of Silver Wolf's ATK to a single enemy.

skills.name: Allow Changes?
skills.simple_desc: There is a high chance to apply additional Type Weaknesses to a single enemy and deals Quantum DMG to this target enemy.
skills.desc:
There is a 82% base chance to add 1 Weakness of an on-field character's Type to the target enemy. This also reduces the enemy's DMG RES to that Weakness Type by 20% for 2 turn(s). If the enemy already has that Type Weakness, the effect of DMG RES reduction to that Weakness Type will not be triggered.
Each enemy can only have 1 Weakness implanted by Silver Wolf. When Silver Wolf implants another Weakness to the target, only the most recent implanted Weakness will be kept.
In addition, there is a 100% base chance to further reduce the All-Type RES of the enemy by 9.4% for 2 turn(s).
Deals Quantum DMG equal to 171% of Silver Wolf's ATK to this enemy.

skills.name: User Banned
skills.simple_desc: Has a high chance of lowering a single enemy's DEF and deals massive Quantum DMG to this target enemy.
skills.desc: There's a 94% base chance to decrease the target enemy's DEF by 41.6% for 3 turn(s). And at the same time, deals Quantum DMG equal to 323% of Silver Wolf's ATK to the target enemy.

skills.name: Awaiting System Response...
skills.simple_desc: After each attack, there is a chance of inflicting the attacked enemy with 1 random Bug.
skills.desc:
Silver Wolf can create three types of Bugs: reduce ATK by 8.8%, reduce DEF by 7.0%, and reduce SPD by 5.2%.
Every time Silver Wolf attacks, she has a 69% base chance to implant a random Bug that lasts for 3 turn(s) in an enemy target.

skills.name: Force Quit Program
skills.simple_desc: Attacks the enemy. After entering battle, deals minor amounts of DMG to all enemies and reduces Toughness of all enemies irrespective of Weakness Types.
skills.desc: Immediately attacks the enemy. After entering battle, deals Quantum DMG equal to 80% of Silver Wolf's ATK to all enemies, and ignores Weakness Types and reduces Toughness from all enemies. Enemies with their Weakness Broken in this way will trigger the Quantum Weakness Break effect.
